Benchopt

description
Benchmark amortized simulation-based inference (SBI) algorithms. Datasets: - train/test: parameter-observation pairs from the prior-simulator joint distribution :math:`p(\theta, x)=p(\theta)p(x|\theta)`. - reference (optional): observations math:`x_ref` and corresponding samples from the reference posterior :math:`p(\theta|x_ref)` (if available). Solvers: amortized SBI algorithms trained on the joint to approximate the posterior :math:`p(\theta|x)` for any observation :math:`x`. Metrics: - expected negative log likelihood (NLL) on test (stopping criterion) and train datasets. - C2ST, EMD, MMD on reference dataset (optional).
